        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 3:47PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Agness, or 27 miles northwest of Cave Junction,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Curry
and northwestern Josephine Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
